readability_reflection: I found string interpolation more readable because it had a more simplistic, efficient way of understanding versus string concatenation, which felt like it was trying to be dumbed down. I think it ultimately made it more difficult to understand.
comprehension_debugging: Both gave me different challenges and advantages, especially in the tasks with a mixture. When it came to numbers, I found it hard to know what format they would be in for both techniques.
preference_rationale: I would rather use string interpolation because I found it more organized and efficient.
learning_curve: I haven't had much experience with both techniques.
